						<summary>

						<p>On the south base of the central shrine, Kailāśanāthasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 15: 986 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a gift of golden fore-head plate for the god Śrī-Kailāyam-uḍaiya Mahādēva at Śrī Sembiyaṉmahādēvi-chaturvēdimaṅgalam, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Aḷa-nāḍu, created by Śrī-Parāntaka-Mādēvaḍigaḷ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Sembiyaṉ Mahādēviyār, the mother of Uttama-chōḷa, by Bhaṭṭaṉ Dāṉatoṅgiyār the queen of Uttama-chōḷa.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 381. </p>						

						</summary>
